FBIS4-10672 "drlat073_a_94017" FBIS-LAT-94-073 Daily Report 14 Apr 1994 Caribbean Cuba Teaching Contingent Receives Anniversary Message Teaching Contingent Receives Anniversary Message FL1504005994 Havana Radio Rebelde Network in Spanish 2300 GMT 14 Apr 94 FL1504005994 Havana Radio Rebelde Network Spanish BFN [Text] Commander in Chief Fidel Castro, first secretary of the Central Committee of the Communist Party of Cuba and president of the Councils of State and Ministers, sent a message to the Third Manuel Ascunce Domenech Teaching Contingent, urging the contingent to continue defending the Revolution's achievements. The letter was sent on the occasion of a provincial ceremony in Pinar del Rio commemorating the contingent's 20th anniversary. Education Minister Luis Ignacio Gomez was present at the ceremony.
